{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"10b4da0e-cf42-4b12-acc7-e8d7b2f6d325","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Gu5zCbwKFzteAAV5E4cCei","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01HKEmBh3dhLzT8BPRXQZeEG","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-0a7160cdd03b4163b81b2bc693fe570f && dotnet nuget search xunit.v3 --take 5 2>/dev/null | head -20","description":"Search for xunit.v3 package version","initial_wait":15},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Search for xunit.v3 package version"}],"interactionId":"1455c1ed-2627-4a79-b720-d11a51de2a3d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me plan the xUnit v2 → v3 migration:\n\n1. **Project file changes**:\n   - Replace `xunit` (v2) with `xunit.v3` (v3)\n   - Remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` (v3 doesn't need it; tests are executables)\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (not needed for v3)\n   - Change SDK to `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` → keep it, but add `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` since xUnit v3 test projects are standalone executables\n   - The target framework can stay at net8.0\n\n2. **Code changes**:\n   - The namespace remains `Xunit` for test attributes like `[Fact]` and `[Theory]`, so no import changes needed\n   - The key difference is switching from the `xunit` package to `xunit.v3`\n   - The runner is now built-in, so I can remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n   - Test projects need to become executables with an entry point and require `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` support\n   - xUnit v3 uses source generators to auto-generate the entry point, so I don't need to manually create a `Program.cs` file\n   - The project output type needs to be set to `Exe`\n   - `Assert` stays in the `Xunit` namespace\n\nNow I'm realizing the attribute signatures have shifted in v3 — `FactAttribute` and `TheoryAttribute` constructors work differently, and assertion methods might return values instead of being void. I should also reconsider the `global.json` configuration since xUnit v3 switched to Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead of VSTest, so that runner setting probably needs updating. Let me verify what the current xunit.v3 version actually is.","outputTokens":1278,"requestId":"CFC9:1FFE72:648F817:703851D:69EC1C8C"},"id":"217ef261-fd9f-4148-be07-f144b584c325","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:45:08.815Z","parentId":"c56f6cac-4322-47a1-a19a-380b02f38f4e"}
